I forgot you live there.

756
00:41:36,600 --> 00:41:39,740
I didn't realize that you
had already moved in.

757
00:41:39,910 --> 00:41:43,540
Kevin, stop it. I'm on the phone
with your mother! I'm sorry, Viola.

758
00:41:43,720 --> 00:41:45,810
The slut's practically
fornicating with him!

759
00:41:45,980 --> 00:41:47,210
- Stop it!
- I don't blame her.

760
00:41:47,390 --> 00:41:48,680
That boy's a fine piece of ass.

761
00:41:48,850 --> 00:41:52,140
Hold on, Viola.
He's... stop it! Right here.

762
00:41:52,310 --> 00:41:54,040
Actually, Charlie,
the reason I'm calling

763
00:41:54,220 --> 00:41:56,680
is I wondered if you'd
like to have lunch next week.

764
00:41:56,850 --> 00:42:00,220
- Really?
- How would Tuesday work for you?

765
00:42:00,400 --> 00:42:02,790
Yeah,
Tuesday's perfect!

766
00:42:02,960 --> 00:42:05,650
Listen, Viola, I'm kind of in the middle
of something right now,

767
00:42:05,830 --> 00:42:07,620
but Tuesday's fine.

768
00:42:07,790 --> 00:42:09,350
Yeah, me too.

769
00:42:09,530 --> 00:42:12,520
- Lots to do!
- Okay, bye!

770
00:42:17,870 --> 00:42:20,500
I'll go get the vodka.

771
00:42:32,810 --> 00:42:34,700
It's good to see you.

772
00:42:34,880 --> 00:42:36,870
There she is.

773
00:42:40,850 --> 00:42:43,320
Charlotte.

774
00:42:43,500 --> 00:42:46,560
Hi. I'm going to have
the garden salad

775
00:42:46,730 --> 00:42:50,450
and the low-cal Chinese dressing
and a decaf iced tea.

776
00:42:50,630 --> 00:42:53,090
- And you, miss?
- I'll just have a...

777
00:42:53,260 --> 00:42:56,390
cheeseburger
with fries and a soda.

778
00:42:56,570 --> 00:42:57,930
- All right.
- Okay.

779
00:42:58,100 --> 00:43:00,660
You continue
to surprise me.

780
00:43:00,830 --> 00:43:03,660
Aren't you worried about fitting
in your wedding dress?

781
00:43:03,840 --> 00:43:06,530
Well, I mean, I'm making the dress
to fit my body,

782
00:43:06,700 --> 00:43:08,070
not the other way
around.

783
00:43:08,250 --> 00:43:10,910
Whoa. I wish I had been
that confident when I got married.

784
00:43:11,080 --> 00:43:13,540
I'll tell you one thing
you're gonna have that I never did,

785
00:43:13,720 --> 00:43:15,510
a stupendous wedding.

786
00:43:15,680 --> 00:43:19,240
And it's important that we
book the church right away.

787
00:43:19,420 --> 00:43:22,280
I always thought
that Kevin looked like Jesus

788
00:43:22,450 --> 00:43:25,110
in the cathedral down
on Second Street. Mmm.

789
00:43:26,980 --> 00:43:29,240
Actually, we were thinking
of having...

790
00:43:29,420 --> 00:43:31,410
a non-denominational
service,

791
00:43:31,580 --> 00:43:34,280
being that I'm more spiritual
than religious.

792
00:43:37,070 --> 00:43:39,090
What about my place then?

793
00:43:39,260 --> 00:43:41,420
That way we don't even
need to book a location.

794
00:43:41,600 --> 00:43:43,630
And Kevin was born there
and grew up there.

795
00:43:43,800 --> 00:43:46,290
It would mean
so much to him. I'll plan it all.

796
00:43:46,470 --> 00:43:49,830
We'll have that marvelous band
that the Swansons' had at their wedding.

797
00:43:50,000 --> 00:43:51,760
And a divine cake.
Oh, honey!

798
00:43:51,930 --> 00:43:53,790
No no no!
Tsk tsk tsk!

799
00:43:53,970 --> 00:43:55,940
Chewing,
it's a disgusting habit.

800
00:43:57,040 --> 00:43:58,670
Hold still.
I've gotta... gotta...

801
00:43:58,850 --> 00:44:00,240
- There! Got it!
- Ow!

802
00:44:00,410 --> 00:44:03,430
Thanks...

803
00:44:03,610 --> 00:44:05,710
What do you think
about peach?

804
00:44:07,480 --> 00:44:09,540
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

805
00:44:09,710 --> 00:44:11,470
Can I get another salad
without the nuts?

806
00:44:11,650 --> 00:44:13,440
- I have allergies.
- Okay.

807
00:44:13,610 --> 00:44:16,200
I'm allergic to nuts,
and eggs, and shellfish,

808
00:44:16,380 --> 00:44:18,680
and blueberries.
... and soy.

809
00:44:18,850 --> 00:44:22,050
It's amazing you've been able
to nourish yourself all these years.

810
00:44:23,230 --> 00:44:24,920
Oh, yeah!
The cake!

811
00:44:25,090 --> 00:44:28,880
I'm thinking traditional vanilla
with strawberry drizzle.

812
00:44:29,060 --> 00:44:33,160
Look, Viola, I really do
have all of this under control.

813
00:44:33,330 --> 00:44:34,690
I made this for you.

814
00:44:34,860 --> 00:44:37,660
It's your wedding planner book.
Peach.

815
00:44:41,630 --> 00:44:43,330
Is that a picture
of me and Kevin?

816
00:44:43,500 --> 00:44:46,920
And... present time
from your new mama!

817
00:44:47,100 --> 00:44:48,930
Thanks.

818
00:44:54,880 --> 00:44:57,840
Wow!

819
00:44:58,020 --> 00:45:00,710
It's big! You can see
the thorns on the roses.

820
00:45:00,880 --> 00:45:03,240
You'll wear it on your wedding day,
just like I did.

821
00:45:03,420 --> 00:45:05,820
Of course I was
a virgin when I wed.

822
00:45:05,990 --> 00:45:08,510
But we'll just pretend
with you.

823
00:45:08,680 --> 00:45:10,370
Now, about the wedding...

824
00:45:10,550 --> 00:45:12,980
the two of you are going to arrive
in a horse and carriage.

825
00:45:13,150 --> 00:45:16,240
And the driver's top-hat
will match the horse's saddles,

826
00:45:16,420 --> 00:45:17,860
and the ribbons
on the doves

827
00:45:18,030 --> 00:45:20,820
that will be released
at the exact moment

828
00:45:21,000 --> 00:45:23,940
of "I do," hmm?

829
00:45:25,230 --> 00:45:27,530
And I've been in touch
with your bridesmaids.

830
00:45:27,710 --> 00:45:29,130
How do you know
their names?

831
00:45:29,300 --> 00:45:31,860
Well, Kevin told me.
And I think for the honeymoon

832
00:45:32,030 --> 00:45:34,560
St. Bart's is the absolute
best place for you to go

833
00:45:34,740 --> 00:45:36,700
- 'cause Kevin adores it.
- Hey, just hold on!

834
00:45:36,870 --> 00:45:38,530
Just wait
a minute, okay?

835
00:45:40,770 --> 00:45:42,440
No.

836
00:45:42,610 --> 00:45:44,570
Thank you, but no.

837
00:45:44,750 --> 00:45:47,340
Thank you,
but no to everything.

838
00:45:47,510 --> 00:45:50,470
No to the horse
and buggy.

839
00:45:50,650 --> 00:45:53,310
No to the top-hats,
and to the doves and geese

840
00:45:53,480 --> 00:45:56,110
and any other farm animals
you're thinking of using that day.

841
00:45:56,280 --> 00:45:58,570
And definitely no to you
planning our honeymoon.

842
00:45:58,750 --> 00:45:59,840
- What?
- Oh no.

843
00:46:00,010 --> 00:46:01,110
I can...

844
00:46:01,290 --> 00:46:03,850
- Oh oh!
- What's wrong?

845
00:46:04,020 --> 00:46:05,750
- "Oh no" what?
- My pills, my pills!

846
00:46:05,930 --> 00:46:06,950
Okay.
Well, let me help you.

847
00:46:07,120 --> 00:46:09,450
- Viola!

848
00:46:09,630 --> 00:46:11,360
- Oh, no!
- Wait, Viola!

849
00:46:11,530 --> 00:46:14,950
Viola!

850
00:46:15,120 --> 00:46:17,650
Oh my God, Viola.
Oh my God!

851
00:46:17,830 --> 00:46:19,520
- Give her some room.
- Help!

852
00:46:19,690 --> 00:46:22,160
- Give her some air.
- My God, is she dead?

853
00:46:22,340 --> 00:46:24,130
- No!
- Get her some help.

854
00:46:24,300 --> 00:46:26,290
It couldn't be
that easy.

855
00:46:31,010 --> 00:46:32,700
She's had
an anxiety attack,

856
00:46:32,870 --> 00:46:34,800
which can feel like
a heart attack.

857
00:46:34,980 --> 00:46:36,340
She's gonna be okay.

858
00:46:36,510 --> 00:46:39,940
But she definitely needs
to take it easy. No stress.

859
00:46:40,110 --> 00:46:42,900
She said that you were
yelling at her,

860
00:46:43,080 --> 00:46:46,540
that you refused her gift
and said she couldn't plan our wedding.

861
00:46:46,710 --> 00:46:49,140
Tell me that's
not true.

862
00:46:49,320 --> 00:46:51,980
Well, technically...

863
00:46:52,150 --> 00:46:53,150
yes.

864
00:46:53,330 --> 00:46:55,820
But, hold on.
I didn't yell at her.

865
00:46:55,990 --> 00:46:58,080
And she just kept pushing
and pushing and pushing.

866
00:46:58,260 --> 00:47:00,850
And, okay, I admit it.
I snapped a little bit. But...

867
00:47:01,020 --> 00:47:03,650
What was I supposed to do?
She wouldn't take no for an answer.

868
00:47:03,820 --> 00:47:06,280
Come on, look, you know
what a hard time she's been having.

869
00:47:06,460 --> 00:47:08,250
- So she's a little difficult.
- Difficult?

870
00:47:08,420 --> 00:47:09,590
A two-year-old
is difficult.

871
00:47:09,760 --> 00:47:11,720
- She's like... ah!
- Come on, she's all alone.

872
00:47:11,890 --> 00:47:13,580
I'm all she's got...
we're all she's got.

873
00:47:13,760 --> 00:47:15,790
Come on.

874
00:47:15,960 --> 00:47:17,150
Excuse me.

875
00:47:17,330 --> 00:47:19,620
I'm Dr. Chamberlain,
the psychiatrist in residence.

876
00:47:19,790 --> 00:47:21,050
- Are you Mrs. Fields's son?
- Yes.

877
00:47:21,220 --> 00:47:23,610
- May we speak in private?
- Actually, this is my fiance.

878
00:47:23,790 --> 00:47:25,320
We can talk.
Is she okay?

879
00:47:25,490 --> 00:47:28,390
Well, I just completed your mother's
interview and I'm concerned.

880
00:47:28,570 --> 00:47:32,160
It's possible that she's on the verge
of a psychotic break.

881
00:47:32,330 --> 00:47:35,990
I should probably see her
at least twice a week, minimum.

882
00:47:36,170 --> 00:47:38,700
Also, I prescribed her
some anti-anxiety medication.

883
00:47:38,870 --> 00:47:41,260
If she starts to feel
overwhelmed, they'll relax her.

884
00:47:41,440 --> 00:47:42,770
Does she live alone?

885
00:47:42,940 --> 00:47:44,030
Yeah.

886
00:47:44,200 --> 00:47:46,060
Well, I feel
it would be best

887
00:47:46,240 --> 00:47:47,870
if she were cared for
by relatives...

888
00:47:48,040 --> 00:47:50,170
people that are closest
to her during this time.

889
00:47:50,350 --> 00:47:52,580
Just until we're confident
that she's out of danger.

890
00:47:52,750 --> 00:47:55,180
All right.
Well, thank you, Doctor.

891
00:47:56,420 --> 00:47:58,380
Oh, God.

892
00:47:58,550 --> 00:48:00,170
I've got that
medical conference.

893
00:48:00,350 --> 00:48:01,540
What am I gonna do?

894
00:48:01,710 --> 00:48:04,540
You know what?
Don't... don't worry about it.

895
00:48:04,710 --> 00:48:07,370
I'll take care of her.

896
00:48:09,850 --> 00:48:11,350
Thank you.

897
00:48:11,520 --> 00:48:13,080
- Come on.
- What?

898
00:48:13,260 --> 00:48:15,260
- No, come with me.
- No no, the doctor said no stress.

899
00:48:15,430 --> 00:48:18,660
- Charlie, come on. Enough already.
- I'll stay here. Kevin!

900
00:48:21,440 --> 00:48:22,960
Come on.

901
00:48:26,830 --> 00:48:28,830
I am so sorry.

902
00:48:29,010 --> 00:48:31,130
No, Mom, don't be.
It's okay, really.

903
00:48:31,300 --> 00:48:32,290
Charlie?

904
00:48:34,300 --> 00:48:36,490
I'm sorry too, Viola.

905
00:48:36,670 --> 00:48:38,940
No, I was too pushy.

906
00:48:40,140 --> 00:48:41,500
No.

907
00:48:41,680 --> 00:48:43,980
You weren't.
Look, Viola...

908
00:48:44,150 --> 00:48:47,810
I would love it if you would
help me with the wedding.

909
00:48:47,990 --> 00:48:50,550
It's all right,
sweetheart, I...

910
00:48:50,720 --> 00:48:52,670
I don't really think
I'm up to it.

911
00:48:52,840 --> 00:48:54,710
My nerves are shot.

912
00:48:57,850 --> 00:48:59,510
Mom...

913
00:49:01,220 --> 00:49:03,980
Mom, Charlie and I think
you should live with us for a while,

914
00:49:04,160 --> 00:49:05,830
until you feel better.

915
00:49:06,000 --> 00:49:07,830
Are you sure?

916
00:49:12,270 --> 00:49:14,360
I can't possibly.

917
00:49:14,530 --> 00:49:16,330
- I couldn't.
- Mom, it's okay. Relax.

918
00:49:18,310 --> 00:49:20,170
I couldn't possibly.

919
00:49:21,770 --> 00:49:24,260
Not unless I know
Charlotte's forgiven me.

920
00:49:25,600 --> 00:49:27,400
Will you?

921
00:49:28,580 --> 00:49:29,630
Me?

922
00:49:29,800 --> 00:49:31,790
Yeah, I forgive you.

923
00:49:37,080 --> 00:49:39,950
You just put those
anywhere.

924
00:49:43,090 --> 00:49:44,880
- Hi!
- Hi.

925
00:49:45,060 --> 00:49:47,250
- Are you feeling better?
- I'm much better, thank you.

926
00:49:47,420 --> 00:49:49,320
- Great.
- Sweetheart, I'm kind of thirsty.

927
00:49:49,500 --> 00:49:51,520
- Would you... is the kitchen over there?
- Yeah, sure.

928
00:49:51,690 --> 00:49:54,020
- Great. Goodbye.
- Okay.

929
00:49:55,220 --> 00:49:57,580
- Hey, Charlie.
- Are you moving in, too?

930
00:49:57,760 --> 00:49:59,450
No, I don't like
the neighborhood.

931
00:49:59,620 --> 00:50:01,790
Look, do you have any
firearms in the house?

932
00:50:01,970 --> 00:50:05,100
- No.
- You might want to get one.

933
00:50:10,840 --> 00:50:13,200
When will you be back?

934
00:50:13,380 --> 00:50:16,340
Soon as I can, honey.
I promise.

935
00:50:16,510 --> 00:50:18,470
Are you sure
you're gonna be okay?

936
00:50:18,650 --> 00:50:21,540
Yeah. I mean, hey,
it's only at night, right?

937
00:50:21,710 --> 00:50:23,910
And, I mean, she's gonna
sleep most of the time

938
00:50:24,080 --> 00:50:26,740
with those pills
the doctor gave her. Right?

939
00:50:26,920 --> 00:50:29,380
Look, I know my mom can be
a little challenging.

940
00:50:29,550 --> 00:50:31,610
So if you have any
problems just call me.

941
00:50:31,790 --> 00:50:33,590
I'm on the first flight back,
I promise.

942
00:50:33,760 --> 00:50:35,780
Okay.
Well, hurry home.

943
00:50:35,960 --> 00:50:37,650
And who knows?
By the time I get back,

944
00:50:37,820 --> 00:50:40,080
maybe you two
will be best friends.

945
00:50:40,260 --> 00:50:41,990
Am I interrupting
something?

946
00:50:42,160 --> 00:50:44,020
- No, Mom, come in.
- The caterer called.

947
00:50:44,190 --> 00:50:45,880
He still thinks
I'm doing the wedding.

948
00:50:46,060 --> 00:50:48,890
He sent over a sample plate
'cause I gave him the colors you wanted.

949
00:50:49,060 --> 00:50:50,960
I said absolutely no peach.

950
00:50:51,140 --> 00:50:55,430
And from now on, everything
goes through my new daughter.

951
00:50:55,600 --> 00:50:57,190
- Thank you.
- Yeah?

952
00:50:57,370 --> 00:50:58,700
Okay, I'll be
right down, thanks.

953
00:50:58,870 --> 00:51:02,560
- Here. Look.
- It's beautiful, Viola.

954
00:51:02,740 --> 00:51:04,870
- Thank you.
- I'm glad you like it.

955
00:51:05,040 --> 00:51:06,760
- Thanks.
- My car's here. Gotta go.

956
00:51:06,930 --> 00:51:08,130
- Bye, Mom. Bye, Mom.
- Okay.

957
00:51:08,310 --> 00:51:10,830
Bye, sweetie.
It's gonna be fun.

958
00:51:11,000 --> 00:51:12,970
- We're gonna have such a good time.
- I love you.

959
00:51:13,150 --> 00:51:15,180
- I'll be a good roommate. I promise.
- Okay.

960
00:51:17,620 --> 00:51:20,910
It's so nice
to have a girlfriend.

961
00:51:49,080 --> 00:51:50,540
Viola?

962
00:51:50,710 --> 00:51:54,150
- Are you all right?
- I can't sleep.

963
00:51:56,760 --> 00:51:58,650
I feel so alone.

964
00:51:58,820 --> 00:52:00,510
I do.

965
00:52:00,680 --> 00:52:02,650
You're not alone.
I'm here.

966
00:52:04,120 --> 00:52:06,810
Did you take
your pills?

967
00:52:06,980 --> 00:52:10,290
My pills?
Oh no, I forgot.

968
00:52:10,470 --> 00:52:12,660
Could you get them
for me, sweetie?

969
00:52:12,830 --> 00:52:14,590
They're on the sink.

970
00:52:14,770 --> 00:52:16,760
Sure.

971
00:52:24,170 --> 00:52:25,690
Here they are.

972
00:52:27,040 --> 00:52:29,240
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

973
00:52:29,410 --> 00:52:32,070
I don't have any water.
Could you get me some water please?

974
00:52:32,240 --> 00:52:34,460
Okay.

975
00:52:34,640 --> 00:52:37,110
I can't drink out
of the tap.

976
00:52:38,150 --> 00:52:41,240
Would you get me some Evian...
with ice?

977
00:52:42,260 --> 00:52:43,660
Yeah.

978
00:52:51,990 --> 00:52:53,020
Here you go.

979
00:52:53,200 --> 00:52:54,860
Thank you.

980
00:52:57,290 --> 00:52:59,060
You have a good night,
okay?

981
00:53:00,530 --> 00:53:01,930
Charlotte?

982
00:53:02,100 --> 00:53:03,720
I hate to ask you this,

983
00:53:03,890 --> 00:53:05,980
but it's my
first night here.

984
00:53:06,160 --> 00:53:08,500
Could you stay with me?

985
00:53:08,670 --> 00:53:10,300
Please?

986
00:53:10,480 --> 00:53:12,910
Sleep with me.
Be a good girl.

987
00:53:15,770 --> 00:53:17,470
No no no!

988
00:53:17,650 --> 00:53:20,210
No no, don't!

989
00:53:21,840 --> 00:53:23,670
God! Viola!

990
00:53:23,850 --> 00:53:25,980
- Are you okay?
- No, let go of me, you!

991
00:53:29,050 --> 00:53:31,540
No.

992
00:53:46,160 --> 00:53:48,090
Okay. Okay.

993
00:54:10,050 --> 00:54:12,720
Hi, how was your day?

994
00:54:12,890 --> 00:54:14,350
It was... okay.

995
00:54:14,530 --> 00:54:16,060
Wonderful!

996
00:54:16,230 --> 00:54:17,420
You're cooking.

997
00:54:17,600 --> 00:54:20,390
I wanted to make you
dinner all by myself.

998
00:54:20,560 --> 00:54:22,220
- Sit.
- Okay.

999
00:54:25,570 --> 00:54:27,260
It's steak
and kidney pie.

1000
00:54:27,430 --> 00:54:30,420
Actually, the steak didn't defrost
in time so it's mostly kidney.

1001
00:54:30,590 --> 00:54:32,350
Mmm!

1002
00:54:32,530 --> 00:54:34,520
- Do you like it?
