at the bride.

1588
01:24:09,540 --> 01:24:10,900
Holy Toledo!

1589
01:24:11,070 --> 01:24:13,900
You are a stunner!

1590
01:24:14,080 --> 01:24:15,970
My grandson
is a lucky fellah.

1591
01:24:16,140 --> 01:24:17,180
Look, what he did.

1592
01:24:17,350 --> 01:24:21,940
He went out and found
himself an exotic Latina!

1593
01:24:23,120 --> 01:24:24,980
Would that my son
had been that lucky.

1594
01:24:25,150 --> 01:24:26,580
Here we go again.

1595
01:24:26,760 --> 01:24:29,550
What? You were
a television weatherwoman

1596
01:24:29,720 --> 01:24:30,740
in Dubuque, Montana.

1597
01:24:30,920 --> 01:24:33,050
You drove around
in a broken-down minivan

1598
01:24:33,220 --> 01:24:36,520
and you drank red wine
from a box!

1599
01:24:39,160 --> 01:24:40,290
Classy.

1600
01:24:40,460 --> 01:24:42,160
You killed him,
you know?

1601
01:24:42,330 --> 01:24:44,020
- What?!
- You killed him.

1602
01:24:44,200 --> 01:24:45,890
All the doctors agreed,

1603
01:24:46,060 --> 01:24:49,320
my son died
of terminal disappointment!

1604
01:24:49,500 --> 01:24:51,360
If anybody killed him,
you did.

1605
01:24:51,530 --> 01:24:53,020
You smothered him
to death!

1606
01:24:53,200 --> 01:24:54,970
Nobody was ever
good enough for him!

1607
01:24:56,900 --> 01:24:58,890
My God, you look old!

1608
01:25:00,540 --> 01:25:01,900
Fine.

1609
01:25:02,070 --> 01:25:04,710
This woman is going
to drive me insane.

1610
01:25:04,880 --> 01:25:08,280
Now, I'd rather not
take all the credit.

1611
01:25:11,990 --> 01:25:13,480
You'll get over it.

1612
01:25:16,020 --> 01:25:18,350
- Okay, I love you.
- You're kidding.

1613
01:25:31,800 --> 01:25:34,100
This is never gonna end, is it?

1614
01:25:34,270 --> 01:25:37,360
I mean, that's going
to be me and you in 30 years.

1615
01:25:37,540 --> 01:25:40,700
We'll be doing
the exact same thing.

1616
01:25:43,500 --> 01:25:45,500
You know what?

1617
01:25:47,180 --> 01:25:50,340
I wanted to marry Kevin
because we make each other happy.

1618
01:25:50,510 --> 01:25:53,240
But you're never gonna
let that happen.

1619
01:25:53,410 --> 01:25:55,410
Are you?

1620
01:25:57,660 --> 01:26:00,560
Oh my God.
I can't believe I'm saying this.

1621
01:26:05,320 --> 01:26:07,520
You win, Viola.

1622
01:26:08,800 --> 01:26:10,490
What do you mean?

1623
01:26:10,660 --> 01:26:12,180
The wedding's off.

1624
01:26:13,700 --> 01:26:15,690
Bye, Ruby.

1625
01:26:18,630 --> 01:26:21,220
I- I cannot believe
she compared me to Gertrude.

1626
01:26:21,400 --> 01:26:24,110
I know.
Now that's just wrong.

1627
01:26:24,280 --> 01:26:26,640
- Thank you.
- You are far worse.

1628
01:26:26,810 --> 01:26:29,830
I don't recall Gertrude
ever trying to poison you.

1629
01:26:30,010 --> 01:26:32,210
And I'm pretty sure
she wore black to your wedding.

1630
01:26:32,380 --> 01:26:34,400
Black. Yeah, she said
she was in mourning.

1631
01:26:34,580 --> 01:26:36,170
Mm-hmm.

1632
01:26:36,340 --> 01:26:38,700
I just want my son
to be happy.

1633
01:26:38,880 --> 01:26:41,910
Whatever made you
think he wasn't?

1634
01:26:50,590 --> 01:26:52,310
Hey, what are you
doing here?

1635
01:26:52,490 --> 01:26:54,960
Don't you know it's
bad luck to see the...

